To diagnose pancreatitis, consider: (1) Symptoms: epigastric pain, nausea/vomiting. (2) Physical exam: epigastric tenderness, fever, jaundice. (3) Labs: elevated amylase/lipase, elevated WBC/CRP; severity markers: hematocrit, BUN, triglycerides, calcium, Na/K. (4) Imaging: pancreatic inflammation, peripancreatic fluid collection.